MetaData.Company Description: Elite DhobiLite is a laundry and dry cleaning service provider that offers convenient and high-quality laundry solutions to customers. With a focus on customer satisfaction, they provide services such as wash and fold, dry cleaning, and ironing, ensuring that clothes are cleaned and cared for with the utmost attention to detail. Their user-friendly platform allows customers to schedule pickups and deliveries, making laundry hassle-free. Apart from that we provide free pickup and delivery services, ensuring that customers can enjoy the convenience of having their laundry taken care of without leaving their homes.
MetaData.Our Business Model: Elite DhobiLite operates on a B2C (Business-to-Consumer) model, providing laundry and dry cleaning services directly to individual customers. The company focuses on delivering high-quality cleaning solutions, convenience, and exceptional customer service. Customers can easily schedule pickups and deliveries through the platform, making it a hassle-free experience. The business model emphasizes customer satisfaction and aims to build long-term relationships with clients by offering reliable and efficient laundry services.
MetaData.Our franchising model: Elite DhobiLite's franchising model allows aspiring entrepreneurs to partner with the brand and operate their own laundry and dry cleaning businesses under the Elite DhobiLite name. Franchisees benefit from the established brand reputation, proven business processes, and ongoing support from the company. The model typically includes training, marketing assistance, and access to a comprehensive operational framework. Franchisees can leverage the company's expertise to successfully run their businesses while contributing to the growth of the Elite DhobiLite brand.

typesOfFranchises.title: Master Franchise
typesOfFranchises.description: A Master Franchise acts as a central processing hub for multiple Retail franchises. Once customer orders are collected by the Retail units, they are sent to the Master Franchise for all major laundry operations such as washing, dry cleaning, ironing, and packing. The cleaned items are then sent back to the respective Retail franchises for final delivery. Typically located in large Tier 1 cities with high order volumes and multiple dependent Retail units.It can serve 10-15 Retail franchises, depending on the order volume and capacity of the Master Franchise.

typesOfFranchises.title: Single Unit Franchise / Live Unit
typesOfFranchises.description: A Single Unit or Live Unit Franchise is a standalone laundry facility that operates independently, without any dependent Retail franchises. This type of unit provides showroom-like visibility and is fully equipped with all necessary laundry machinery to handle the complete service cycle. Orders are received directly from runners, and all processes—including washing, dry cleaning, ironing, packing, and delivery—are managed within the unit. Runners are responsible for both picking up laundry from customers and delivering cleaned items back to them, ensuring a direct and efficient workflow. This model is well-suited for areas with moderate demand, enabling comprehensive, end-to-end service from a single location. If a Live Unit is equipped with sufficient machinery to support 3-4 Retail franchises, it is referred to as a hybrid setup.

typesOfFranchises.title: Retail Franchise
typesOfFranchises.description: A Retail Franchise acts as a local customer touchpoint, where runners collect laundry orders from customers and deliver them to the Retail unit. The Retail Franchise then forwards these orders to its associated Master Franchise for all processing tasks, such as washing, dry cleaning, and ironing. After processing, the cleaned items are returned to the Retail unit for final delivery to the customer. This model enhances local accessibility and convenience, with each Retail Franchise typically linked to a nearby Master Franchise for efficient operations.Retail franchises can have only one machine that is steam press machine and they can only do ironing of the cloths and they can not do any other processing like washing or dry cleaning of the cloths, so they are dependent on master center for all the processing tasks.

MetaData.Runner: A Runner is responsible for collecting articles from customers and delivering them to the designated franchise unit (depending on the center type). Once the processing — including washing, dry cleaning, and packing — is completed, the Runner ensures the final delivery of the cleaned garments back to the customer. The Runner plays a crucial role in maintaining customer satisfaction by ensuring timely pickups and deliveries, and they are  the face of the brand during these interactions. Their efficiency and professionalism directly impact the overall customer experience.

Our Order flow / Workflow.Ongoing leads/Team View: when customer place the orders from customer application then the order first arrives in ongoing leads section of Msentinel app (backend application).in ownwer id it will reflect as ongoing leads and in manager id it will reflect as team view.Now the next step is that the owner or manager will assign the order to the respective runner for pickup.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Assigned order: When an order is assigned to a runner by the owner or manager, it appears in the 'Assigned Order' section of the Msentinel app in the runner Id. The runner can view all assigned orders along with customer details such as name, address, and contact number. The runner then accepts the order, confirms the customer's availability at the pickup location, and proceeds to collect the articles or clothes from the customer.
Our Order flow / Workflow.E-challan: When a runner arrives at the customer's location, they can view the assigned order in the Msentinel app. The runner is responsible for safely and securely collecting the items. Upon arrival, the runner must take three mandatory photos of the articles/clothes to be picked up. After this, the E-challan page opens, where the runner first selects the required services and then enters the details of the articles/clothes being collected. This process ensures accurate documentation and tracking of each order.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Invoice generation: After the order is picked up, the runner delivers the items to the appropriate center—either a retail center, live unit, or directly to the master center if handled by the master center's runner. The manager at the center is responsible for generating the final invoice. Before generating the invoice, the manager must cross-verify the picked items with the e-challan created by the runner at pickup. The invoice should only be generated if all items in the e-challan match the items received; if there is any discrepancy, the manager should not proceed and must contact the runner for clarification. Once verified, the invoice is generated in the Msentinel app under the 'Generate Invoice' section and uploaded to the server, which then distributes it as needed, including to the customer.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Tracker/Tagging of the cloths: After the invoice is generated, the order moves to the tracker section of the Msentinel app. Here, there is an option to print the tag for that specific order, as well as options to cancel the order or invoice if needed. Each item is tagged with a unique customer tag ID to ensure accurate tracking and processing. This tagging process is essential for maintaining order accuracy and preventing mix-ups during cleaning and delivery. The tags include information such as the customer tag ID and the count of clothes as per the selected service.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Transit task_Workshop_Hub: After tagging the clothes, the order moves to the 'Transit Task' section (W_Hub) of the Msentinel app. Here, the manager verifies the tagged items against the invoice generated at pickup. Upon successful verification, the Workshop Hub accepts the order for processing. This step ensures all items are accurately accounted for and ready for cleaning. Acceptance by the Workshop(w_hub) confirms that the articles are now under their responsibility for further processing.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Packing application/processing of the cl: Once the articles have been accepted, the order moves to the Msentinel packing application. First, the items are inspected for any damage or issues. If any problem is found, it is recorded in the packing app under the 'problem' section, and the customer is informed.After that, the articles proceed to processing, which includes washing, dry cleaning, ironing, and packing as per the customer's selected services. The workshop ensures all processes are performed efficiently and to high quality standards. After cleaning, the items are packed by the packing staff, and the details are updated in the Msentinel packing application.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Transit Task_Hub: Once packing is completed, the order moves to the Transit Task Runner section (hub) in the Msentinel app. Here, the respective manager verifies the packed items against the invoice generated at pickup. After successful verification, the retail accepts(hub) the packed items. The order is then moved to the Team View section as an unassigned delivery in manager Id and in owner id it will reflect in ongoing leads section, where the manager assigns it to the appropriate runner for final delivery to the customer.
Our Order flow / Workflow.Assigned Order/delivery of the cloths to: Once the order is assigned to a runner for delivery, it appears in the 'Assigned Order' section of the Msentinel app in the Runner Id. The runner can view all details of the order, including customer information and the items to be delivered. The runner then proceeds to deliver the packed items to the customer at the specified address. Upon successful delivery, the runner updates the status in the app, marking the order as completed.Alao the runner will collect the payment from the customer at the time of delivery, if applicable.
Our Order flow / Workflow.ratings given by the customer: After delivery, customers can rate their experience and provide feedback via the customer application . There are two types of ratings: quality rating (reflects the processing center's performance) and PD rating (pickup-delivery, reflects the center where the order was placed). Quality ratings go to the processing/master center, while PD ratings go to the center which is handling the pickup and delivery of the arcticles(retail, master, live, or online).

Terms used in workflow.title: E-Challan
Terms used in workflow.description: An electronic document generated by the runner at the time of pickup, containing details of the items collected and their estimated processing costs. It serves as a preliminary invoice and helps in tracking the order.

Terms used in workflow.title: Invoice
Terms used in workflow.description: A formal bill generated by the manager after verifying the items against the E-Challan. It includes final pricing for the processing of the particular order.

Terms used in workflow.title: Tagging
Terms used in workflow.description: The process of attaching unique identifiers to each item for tracking purposes throughout the processing and delivery stages.

Terms used in workflow.title: Processing
Terms used in workflow.description: The cleaning, dry cleaning, ironing, and packing of items as per customer specifications.

Terms used in workflow.title: Workshop
Terms used in workflow.description: A Workshop is a central processing facility that handles the major laundry operations for multiple Retail franchises. It is responsible for washing, dry cleaning, ironing, and packing articles collected from the Retail units or directly by their own runners. The Workshop ensures that all cleaning processes are carried out efficiently and to the highest quality standards.

Terms used in workflow.title: logistics
Terms used in workflow.description: Transfer of arcticles from one center to another, such as from a Retail franchise to a Workshop or from a Workshop to a Retail franchise for final delivery to the customer.

Revenue share between franchises and com.title: Master Franchise and Retail Franchise
Revenue share between franchises and com.description: The Master Franchise retains 43% of the total revenue generated from the orders processed at its center, while the Retail Franchise also retains 43%. The franchise responsible for handling logistics receives a 7% share of the total revenue. The remaining 7% is allocated to the company as royalty.

Revenue share between franchises and com.title: Single Unit Franchise / Live Unit
Revenue share between franchises and com.description: If it doesnt have any dependent Retail franchises, the Live Unit retains 93% of the total revenue generated from the orders processed at its center. The remaining 7% is allocated to the company as royalty. But if it has dependent Retail franchises then the revenue share will be same as Master Franchise and Retail Franchise.

workAndRevenue.description: A comprehensive overview of the center's work and revenue metrics, including billing, cloth counts, and financial statistics.

Columns.Title: centerId
Columns.description: Unique identifier for each center.

Columns.Title: centerName
Columns.description: Name of the center.

Columns.Title: poc
Columns.description: Point of contact for the center.

Columns.Title: companyLedgerAmount
Columns.description: Monthly settlement amount between the franchise and the company. If positive, the franchise owes this amount to the company; if negative, the company owes this amount to the franchise. (it should be paid by 7th of every month otherwise your center access will be blocked by the system automatically)

Columns.Title: runningcompanyLedgerAmount
Columns.description: The real-time running balance between the franchise and the company. If positive, the franchise owes this amount to the company; if negative, the company owes this amount to the franchise. This value is updated continuously as transactions occur.

Columns.Title: pendingAmountInCenter
Columns.description: The total amount which is pending from the customer end  at the particular center.

Columns.Title: withMeRunners
Columns.description: The total amount currently held by runners, representing collections from customers that have not yet been transferred to the franchise. Franchise owners should regularly review runner 'withMe' transactions and ensure timely transfer of these amounts from runners to the franchise account.

Columns.Title: serviceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount billed for services rendered to customers who have an active subscription or prepaid plan at the center during the current month till the date.

Columns.Title: lyMtdServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount billed for services rendered to customers who have an active subscription or prepaid plan at the center during the same month till the same date last year.

Columns.Title: compensation
Columns.description: Compensation is the amount which is given to the customer in the current month. It can be discounted or free service.

Columns.Title: lastMonthServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount billed for services rendered to customers who have an active subscription or prepaid plan at the center during the last month.

Columns.Title: lyServiceBilling
Columns.description: Total amount billed for services rendered to customers with an active subscription or prepaid plan at the center during the same month last year.

Columns.Title: yearlyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: Total amount billed at the center in the current year till the date divided by 12.

Columns.Title: lyAvgRevenue
Columns.description: Total amount billed at the center during whole  last 1 year divided by 12.

Columns.Title: avgTicketSize
Columns.description: Total amount billed at the center divided by total number of orders in the current month.

Columns.Title: lmAvgTicketSize
Columns.description: Last month total amount billed at the center divided by last month total number of orders.

Columns.Title: yearAvgTicketSize
Columns.description: total  amount billed at the center divided by total number of orders in the current year .

Columns.Title: lastYearAvgTicketSize
Columns.description: total revenue generated last year at the center divided by total number of orders placed last year at the center.
